{'type': 'text/plain', 'language': None, 'base': 'http://export.arxiv.org/api/query?search_query=%22time+series%22&start=0&max_results=1000&sortBy=submittedDate&sortOrder=ascending', 'value': 'I explain how the Lax-Phillips theory can be applied to a purely innovating
time series and compute the corresponding scattering function. I then associate
such a time series to an algebraic curve (of genus at least 1) over a finite
